You are working in the Space4X project. Rendering works (we see the sanity cube from DemoWorldPreflightSystem / TestSpawnSystem), but we don’t see the mining demo cubes yet.

Your task is to create a minimal, ultra-obvious debug demo:

Spawn a few bright cubes near the origin, using the same Demo render path as the sanity cube.

Make those cubes orbit so we see motion.

Log clearly so we know it ran.

1. Copy the known-good render pattern

Open:

Assets/Scripts/Space4x/Demo/TestSpawnSystem.cs

Assets/Shared/Demo/DemoRenderBootstrap.cs (or similar)

Shared.Demo.DemoRenderUtil (where MakeRenderable is defined)

Find the exact call to DemoRenderUtil.MakeRenderable in TestSpawnSystem that creates the sanity cube, e.g.:

DemoRenderUtil.MakeRenderable(
    entityManager,
    entity,
    new float3(0f, 0f, 0f),
    new float3(2f, 2f, 2f),
    new float4(0f, 1f, 1f, 1f));


Whatever the actual signature is, copy that pattern exactly. We want our debug cubes to use the same rendering pipeline.

2. Add a debug tag component

Create a tiny tag to identify debug cubes:

using Unity.Entities;

namespace Space4X.Demo
{
    public struct DebugOrbitTag : IComponentData
    {
    }
}


Put this in Assets/Scripts/Space4x/Demo/DebugOrbitTag.cs or similar.

3. Create a guaranteed-running debug spawner

Create a new file:

Assets/Scripts/Space4x/Demo/Space4XDebugCubeSpawnerSystem.cs

Implement:

using Unity.Entities;
using Unity.Mathematics;
using Unity.Transforms;
using UnityEngine;
using Shared.Demo; // adjust namespace to where DemoRenderUtil lives

namespace Space4X.Demo
{
    [UpdateInGroup(typeof(InitializationSystemGroup))]
    [UpdateAfter(typeof(SharedDemoRenderBootstrap))] // adjust type name if needed
    public partial struct Space4XDebugCubeSpawnerSystem : ISystem
    {
        public void OnCreate(ref SystemState state)
        {
            // Only run once render bootstrap is ready
            state.RequireForUpdate<DemoRenderReady>(); // or whatever marker SharedDemoRenderBootstrap creates
        }

        public void OnUpdate(ref SystemState state)
        {
            var em = state.EntityManager;

            Debug.Log("[Space4XDebugCubeSpawnerSystem] Spawning debug orbit cubes...");

            // Positions near the origin / sanity cube
            var positions = new[]
            {
                new float3(0f, 0f, 3f),
                new float3(3f, 0f, 0f),
                new float3(-3f, 0f, 0f)
            };

            var colors = new[]
            {
                new float4(1f, 0f, 1f, 1f), // magenta
                new float4(1f, 1f, 0f, 1f), // yellow
                new float4(0f, 1f, 0f, 1f)  // green
            };

            for (int i = 0; i < positions.Length; i++)
            {
                var e = em.CreateEntity();

                // Use EXACTLY the same render util & pattern as TestSpawnSystem
                DemoRenderUtil.MakeRenderable(
                    em,
                    e,
                    positions[i],
                    new float3(1.5f, 1.5f, 1.5f),
                    colors[i]);

                // Ensure we have a LocalTransform if DemoRenderUtil doesn't add one
                if (!em.HasComponent<LocalTransform>(e))
                {
                    em.AddComponentData(e, LocalTransform.FromPositionRotationScale(
                        positions[i],
                        quaternion.identity,
                        1.5f));
                }

                em.AddComponent<DebugOrbitTag>(e);
            }

            Debug.Log("[Space4XDebugCubeSpawnerSystem] Spawned " + positions.Length + " debug cubes.");

            // Only run once
            state.Enabled = false;
        }
    }
}


Important: If SharedDemoRenderBootstrap or DemoRenderReady have different names/namespaces in your project, adjust using and [UpdateAfter]/RequireForUpdate to match. Use exactly the same marker type that TestSpawnSystem relies on.

4. Create an orbit system to move them

Create another file:

Assets/Scripts/Space4x/Demo/Space4XDebugCubeOrbitSystem.cs

Implement a simple orbit on the XZ plane:

using Unity.Entities;
using Unity.Mathematics;
using Unity.Transforms;

namespace Space4X.Demo
{
    [UpdateInGroup(typeof(SimulationSystemGroup))]
    public partial struct Space4XDebugCubeOrbitSystem : ISystem
    {
        public void OnUpdate(ref SystemState state)
        {
            float dt = SystemAPI.Time.DeltaTime;
            float angularSpeed = 0.5f; // radians per second

            foreach (var transform in SystemAPI.Query<RefRW<LocalTransform>>()
                                               .WithAll<DebugOrbitTag>())
            {
                var lt = transform.ValueRO;
                float3 pos = lt.Position;

                // Orbit around the origin on XZ
                float2 pos2 = new float2(pos.x, pos.z);
                float r = math.length(pos2);
                if (r < 0.0001f)
                    continue;

                float angle = math.atan2(pos.z, pos.x);
                angle += angularSpeed * dt;

                float2 newPos2 = new float2(math.cos(angle) * r, math.sin(angle) * r);
                lt.Position = new float3(newPos2.x, pos.y, newPos2.y);

                // Optionally, spin them in place too
                lt.Rotation = math.mul(
                    lt.Rotation,
                    quaternion.AxisAngle(math.up(), angularSpeed * dt));

                transform.ValueRW = lt;
            }
        }
    }
}

5. Wire order vs existing demo systems

Make sure Space4XDebugCubeSpawnerSystem doesn’t get gated out:

It already [UpdateAfter(typeof(SharedDemoRenderBootstrap))] and RequireForUpdate<DemoRenderReady>() so it should run right after the demo render bootstrap is ready.

TestSpawnSystem / DemoWorldPreflightSystem can stay as-is; we just add more cubes.

